      "properties": {"Node name for S&R": "Note"},
      "widgets_values": [
        "POST-FX PIPELINE (runs AFTER per-scene I2V render)\n=========================================\n\nPIPELINE ORDER:\n  1. RIFE frame interp  (24fps → 48fps, smoother motion)\n  2. Deflicker           (smooth brightness jumps)\n  3. LUT color grade     (cinematic look applied before upscale)\n  4. 4x UltraSharp upscale\n  5. Pixel cap to 2048px (avoid OOM on 16GB)\n  6. Blend graded + upscaled (50/50 mix)\n  7. Film grain          (subtle, 0.15 intensity)\n  8. Save H.264 CRF 16 @ 48fps\n\nWIDGET NOTES:\n- RIFE: rife47.pth is fastest, rife49.pth is sharpest. multiplier=2 doubles fps.\n- Deflicker: window=16 frames, strength 0.5 (gentle, won't kill strobe FX if you want them)\n- Upscale: 4x-UltraSharp is the gold standard for photoreal. For stylized use 4x_NMKD-Siax.\n- Pixel cap: 2048 = 2K final. Use 4096 for 4K delivery (much slower, OOM risk on big scenes).\n- LUT: 0.9 strength keeps it from looking overly graded. Drop to 0.6-0.7 for subtler looks.\n- Film grain: 0.15 is barely perceptible. 0.25 = visible 35mm look. gaussian = most natural.\n\n16GB VRAM TIPS:\n  • RIFE v4.x needs ~3GB at 832x480 → safe\n  • 4x upscale of 832x480 → 3328x1920 per frame. Pixel cap to 2048 keeps it manageable.\n  • If OOM during upscale: temporarily disconnect grain + blend, render upscale separately.\n  • Disable FilmGrainAdvanced if you prefer to add grain in DaVinci/ffmpeg later.\n\nUSAGE:\n  Run this workflow on EACH scene MP4 produced by 02_scene_render_Wan.json\n  Use batch_render.py with --post-fx flag to chain render+post automatically."
      ],
